Merge pull request #7 from benswift/master

build fixes for OSX 10.8

changes required to build successfully with clang on OSX 10.8

there were a few things required to get it to build on 10.8.  it
should now work at least back to 10.6, but I haven't tested that.

the main additions/changes are:

- shared libraries on osx is use .dylib extension
- add clang flags to build 64-bit dylibs
- added a couple of function prototypes to help clang with inlined
  functions
- add *.dylib pattern to .gitignore
updated telephony plugin ids to be in my new 4701-4740 range; a_law = 4701, u_law = 4702

added u_law and a_law plugins
